IN the end, a react component is a function that returns jsx.
(or html ).  Whether you are using a function or a class, you are
 using jsx

1/ defining a class component (done when definin state)
see app.js in one-app folder
import React, {Component} from 'react';
class App extends Component{
render(){
  return (<div></div>)
  }

2/ defining a function for a component use the es6 way, an arrow function
see Person.js in one-app folder
import React from 'react';
const person=(props)=>{
return(
  <div>
    <p>I'm a {props.name} </p>
</div>
)
}
